        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 6:28PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Arlington, or 16 miles south of Covington, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Arlington, Somerville, Warren, Oakland, Mason, Gallaway, Stanton,
Braden, Asbury, Yum Yum, Belmont, Canaan Grove, Longtown, Moorman,
Keeling, Lambert, Gainesville, Shepp, Powers, and Griffen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
